o, Important Cultural Property) – from the mid-Kamakura period; approximately 3 m tall with carvings of the Manyo and Shakyamuni Buddhas on the tower body. * {{ill|Roppōmitsu-ji|ja|六波羅蜜寺|12=draft}}, Agoya-tsuka (in Kyoto Prefecture) – from the Kamakura period. * {{ill|Chōraku-ji (Ota City)|ja|長楽寺|12=draft}} Pagoda (in Ota City, Gunma Prefecture, Important Cultural Property) – built in the 2nd year of Kenchi (【1276】).
