{ill|Saimei-ji (Kōra-cho, Shiga)|ja|西明寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saimei-ji (Kōra-cho, Shiga)|qq=|1=Saimei-ji (Kōra-cho, Shiga)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11628430}} Pagoda (in Kōra-cho, Shiga Prefecture, Important Cultural Property) – inscribed with the 2nd year of the Jiagen era (【1304】). * [[:en:Ishiyama-dera|Ishiyama-dera]] Stone Pagoda (in Ōtsu, Shiga Prefecture) – from the mid-Kamakura period; currently about 2 m tall, though originally estimated at about 3 m. * Ishiyama-dera “Mekakushi-iwa” (in Shiga Prefecture) – from the Heian period. * {{ill|Anyō-ji (Higashiyama, Kyoto)|ja|安養寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Anyō-ji (Higashiyama, Kyoto)|qq=|1=Anyō-ji (Higashiyama, Kyoto)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11451679}} (with a pagoda attributed to [[:en:Jien|Jien]]) (in Kyoto, Important Cultural Property) – from the mid-Kamakura period; approximately 3 m tall with carvings of the Manyo and Shakyamuni Tathāgata Buddhas on the tower body. * [[:en:Rokuharamitsu-ji|Roppōmitsu-ji]], Agoya-tsuka (in Kyoto Prefecture) – from the Kamakura period. * {{ill|Chōraku-ji (Ota City)|ja|長楽寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chōraku-ji (Ota City)|qq=|1=Chōraku-ji|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11653105}} Pagoda (in Ota City, Gunma Prefecture, Important Cultural Property) – built in the 2nd year of Kenchi (【1276】).
