=== Stone Pagodas === Stone pagodas occupy a major section of the field of [[Stone Art]]. Some stone pagodas feature carved door-like panels or images of two figures (the Manyo Rulai and Shakyamuni Tathāgata) on the cylindrical body. Regional examples include the {{ill|Kunō-tō|ja|国東塔|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunō-tō|qq=|1=Kunō-tō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11420973}} in {{ill|Kunisaki, Ōita|ja|国東|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunisaki, Ōita|qq=|1=Kunisaki, Ōita|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11420970}}, Ōita Prefecture, and the {{ill|Akazaki-tō|ja|赤碕塔|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akazaki-tō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in [[:en:Tottori Prefecture|Tottori Prefecture]]. * [[:en:Kurama-dera|Kurama-dera]] Stone Pagoda (in Kyoto, National Treasure) – an inscribed Buddhist scripture tube bearing the inscription of the Hōan era (【1120】) was discovered buried in the soil beneath the tower. It is considered the oldest extant example of a stone pagoda. * Ruins of {{ill|Kande-ji|ja|関寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kande-ji|qq=|1=Seki-dera|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11655708}}: “Ushi-tō” (Stone Pagoda), (in Shiga Prefecture, Important Cultural Property) – from the late Heian period; 3.3 m tall with an octagonal roof; the ornamental ring atop the roof was added later. It, together with the Kurama-dera pagoda, Ranks among the oldest. * The ruins of the pagoda at {{ill|Mangan-ji|ja|満願寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mangan-ji|qq=|1=Mangan-ji|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11563954}} (in Takashima City, Shiga Prefecture) – from the early Kamakura period; 4 m tall; the ornamental ring was added later. * [[:en:Jōdo-ji|Jōdo-ji (Onomichi)]] Pagoda (in Onomichi, Hiroshima Prefecture, Important Cultural Property) – inscribed with the date of the first year of the Kōan era (【1278】); 2.8 m tall; built using rammed earth on a dais. * {